{"review": [{"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 0, "sentence": "Regularizing RKHS norm is a classic way to prevent overfitting."}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 1, "sentence": "The authors"}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 2, "sentence": "note the connections between RKHS norm and several common regularization and"}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 3, "sentence": "robustness enhancement techniques, including gradient penalty, robust"}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 4, "sentence": "optimization via PGD and spectral norm normalization."}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 5, "sentence": "They can be seen as upper"}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 6, "sentence": "or lower bounds of the RKHS norm."}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 7, "sentence": "There are some interesting findings in the experiments. For example, for"}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 8, "sentence": "improving generalization, using the gradient penalty based method seems to work"}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 9, "sentence": "best."}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 10, "sentence": "For improving robustness, adversarial training with PGD has the best"}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 11, "sentence": "results (which matches the conclusions by Madry et al.); but as shown in Figure"}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 12, "sentence": "2,"}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 13, "sentence": "because adversarial training only decreases a lower bound of RKHS norm, it"}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 14, "sentence": "does not necessarily decrease the upper bound (the product of spectral norms)."}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 15, "sentence": "This can be shown as a weakness of adversarial training if the authors explore"}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 16, "sentence": "further and deeper in this direction."}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 17, "sentence": "Overall, this paper has many interesting results, but its contribution is"}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 18, "sentence": "limited because:"}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 19, "sentence": "1. The regularization techniques in reproducing kernel Hilbert space (RKHS) has"}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 20, "sentence": "been well studied by previous literature."}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 21, "sentence": "This paper simply applies these"}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 22, "sentence": "results to deep neural networks, by treating the neural network as a big"}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 23, "sentence": "black-box function f(x)"}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 24, "sentence": "."}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 25, "sentence": "Many of the results have been already presented in"}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 26, "sentence": "previous works like Bietti & Mairal (2018)."}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 27, "sentence": "2. In experiments, the authors explored many existing methods on improving"}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 28, "sentence": "generalization and robustness. However all these methods are known and not new."}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 29, "sentence": "Ideally, the authors can go further and propose a new regularization method"}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 30, "sentence": "based on the connection between neural networks and RKHS, and conduct"}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 31, "sentence": "experiments to show its effectiveness."}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 32, "sentence": "The paper is overall well written, and the introductions to RKHS and each"}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 33, "sentence": "regularization techniques are very clear."}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 34, "sentence": "The provided experiments also include"}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 35, "sentence": "some interesting findings."}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 36, "sentence": "My major concern is the lack of novel contributions"}, {"text_id": "S1x3WD8ChQ", "sid": 37, "sentence": "in this paper."}], "reviewlabels": [{"text_id": "S1x3WD8